\section*{Problem:}

The Hall coefficient and electrical conductivity of an n-type silicon are given as \( R_H = -7.3 \times 10^{-5} \, \text{m}^3/\text{C} \) and \( \sigma = 2 \times 10^7 \, \text{mho/m} \), respectively. Calculate the magnitude of the mobility of the electrons.

\section*{Solution:}

The mobility \(\mu\) of the electrons can be calculated using the relation:
\[
\mu = \sigma \times |R_H|
\]

Substituting the given values:
\[
\mu = (2 \times 10^7 \, \text{mho/m}) \times (7.3 \times 10^{-5} \, \text{m}^3/\text{C})
\]

\[
\mu = 1.46 \, \text{m}^2/\text{Vs}
\]

\section*{Additional Calculations:}

